I search for new workouts and workout channels every week and always seem to come back to POPSUGAR Fitness. Their workouts are effective and fun and I prefer longer videos (30-45 min) instead of the short ones targeting only one muscle area.

And the most important reason for me is that this channel isnâ€™t as superficial as the usual pilates/workout-channels out there. The name of the videos are not â€œget a sexy butt in 6 minutesâ€ or â€œget long lean legs like *insert celebrity with natural long lean legs here*â€. When they reference to a celebrity itâ€™s to show that the personal trainer is really good (so good that celebrities with a lot of money pay them to train them) and not to make us believe that we will look like the celebrity if we do the workout. At least thatâ€™s how I see it. I just want to give this channel cred for being about working out and feeling good.
